prompt: How do we know other minds exist? (variant 1)
vectorlm_chain:
ψ:gl = evaluate(existence_of_other_minds)
ψ:qs = question(what_evidence_is_available)
ψ:pj = simulate(observer_behaviour → mind_attribution)
ψ:br = links(communication, emotion, reaction)
ψ:tt = inference_of_other_minds = abductive + analogical

prompt: Why do people procrastinate? (variant 1)
vectorlm_chain:
ψ:gl = explain(procrastination_behaviour)
ψ:pj = simulate(fear, perfectionism, reward_deferral)
ψ:cu = explores(possible_future_discomfort)
ψ:fr = anticipates(stress)
ψ:cf = overlaps(ψ:cu, ψ:fr); blocks(action)
ψ:tt = procrastination = emotional_conflict_not_laziness

prompt: Could logic be different in another universe? (variant 1)
vectorlm_chain:
ψ:gl = explore(meta-logic_invariance)
ψ:pj = simulate(logical_axioms_variation)
ψ:wf = alter(law_of_identity or excluded_middle)
ψ:tt = alternative_logics_possible; inference_would_shift

prompt: Can randomness be truly random? (variant 1)
vectorlm_chain:
ψ:gl = evaluate(purity_of_randomness)
ψ:qs = examine(entropy_source)
ψ:pj = simulate(quantum_indeterminacy)
ψ:ft = match(randomness → unpredictability)
ψ:tt = true_randomness = non-deterministic_unpredictability

prompt: Design a cognitive architecture for alien intelligence. (variant 1)
vectorlm_chain:
ψ:gl = construct(alien_cognitive_architecture)
ψ:pj = remove(human_biological_constraints)
ψ:an = map(environment → structure → cognition)
ψ:br = links(sensor_type, logic_type, memory_format)
ψ:tt = cognition = structure_of_interaction_with_world
